xxm values need to be aligned by 16 bytes for you to use a 4 value struct
Every single precision float is 4 bytes.

const char* in fasm do not need [] because they are values passed directly
[] would dereference the address,
the function DrawText(const char* title) expects an address so no []

order of linux abi V:
rdi, rsi, rdx, rcx, r8, r9, r10, r11
